<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1941,2037]" pageId="0" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1941,1966]" pageId="0" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wings hyaline; eyes with a weakly developed impression; male first abdominal tergite with a dorsal conical projection with only few scattered black setae at apex; male pulvinus elongate and placed upper to gonarcus, parameres elongate, curving and acuminate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,383,152,176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
<typeStatus box="[199,308,152,176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">Holotype</typeStatus>
male:
</emphasis>
Head: vertex predominantly dark brown except by yellow lateral stripes bordering the eye; vertex densely covered by white and black setae. Frons brown with long, white pilosity (
<figureCitation box="[1196,1265,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,2010,2033]" captionTargetBox="[203,1362,232,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[185,1409,195,1987]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 1, Head, lateral view; Fig. 2, Antenna apex; Fig. 3, Fore and hindwing (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202497/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1252,1265,188,212]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus and labrum yellow with sparse white setae. Mandible pale yellow at base, becoming black distally. Palpus yellow, except the distal segment dark brown, with long white setae at base; each segment with small black setae distally. Antenna clubbed, relatively short, 
<quantity box="[536,651,295,319]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.552" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="15.52">15.52 mm</quantity>
, only reaching the level of the forewing second Rs fork (wing spread). Scape yellow; pedicel yellow with the apical edge brown covered by long white setae; flagellum with 
<number box="[1285,1313,332,356]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="52.0">52</number>
flagellomeres, the last 
<number box="[296,324,367,391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="15.0">15</number>
forming the club (
<figureCitation box="[531,600,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,2010,2033]" captionTargetBox="[203,1362,232,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[185,1409,195,1987]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 1, Head, lateral view; Fig. 2, Antenna apex; Fig. 3, Fore and hindwing (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202497/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[583,600,367,391]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Each flagellomere with basal half light brown and apical half dark brown except the terminal expanded ones, completely dark brown and covered by small black setae (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1291,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,2010,2033]" captionTargetBox="[203,1362,232,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[185,1409,195,1987]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 1, Head, lateral view; Fig. 2, Antenna apex; Fig. 3, Fore and hindwing (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202497/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1274,1291,404,428]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Eye brown and with a weakly developed transversal line in the middle region (
<figureCitation box="[903,968,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,2010,2033]" captionTargetBox="[203,1362,232,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[185,1409,195,1987]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 1, Head, lateral view; Fig. 2, Antenna apex; Fig. 3, Fore and hindwing (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202497/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[955,968,439,463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">Thorax: covered with scattered white and black setae. Pronotum very reduced, collar-like with lateral extremities yellow, median region brown and remaining dark brown. Mesonotum dark brown except for a narrow longitudinal light brown stripe in the prescutum and a central brown spot in scutellum. Metanotum slightly paler than mesonotum. Pleural sclerites yellow with some light brown spots.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">Legs: coxae, trochanters pale yellow, femora with internal face pale yellow and external face brown, tibiae black with small yellow spots in external face, tarsomeres completely black. White setae covering coxae, trochanters and femora. Tibiae and tarsi with sublateral strong black bristles. Tibia with two large reddish brown spurs at apex. Claws reddish brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[273,341,764,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,2010,2033]" captionTargetBox="[203,1362,232,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[185,1409,195,1987]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 1, Head, lateral view; Fig. 2, Antenna apex; Fig. 3, Fore and hindwing (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202497/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[325,341,764,788]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
): membrane hyaline, veins brown except for the yellow origin of R at wing base, pterostigma with membrane and veins brown, subtriangular with four crossveins, with at least one branched. Rs with seven branches. Forewing with 
<number box="[435,445,836,860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="1.0">1</number>
A very short. Hindwing broader than forewing basally, CuA with a well-developed fork, 
<number box="[151,161,871,895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="1.0">1</number>
A long. Apical area of forewing slightly larger than in the hindwing, both with three rows off cells, but forewing with two cells inserted between the dorsal and the median rows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Abdomen: tergites dark brown with narrow transversal light brown stripe on the posterior margin. Basal half of tergites with two lateral pores. Sternites brown to dark brown, the last ones a little darker. Sclerites covered by small black setae except the first two tergites and sternites, covered by long white setae. First tergite with a dark brown dorsal conical projection which extends until the begging of the third tergite (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1191,1052,1076]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[310,1266,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[310,1267,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 4, Male proximal abdominal tergites, lateral view, setae not represented; Fig. 5, Male, dorsal projection of the first abdominal tergite, dorsal view; Fig. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 7, Male terminalia, lateral view. Ectoproct (ect), paramere (pa), pulvinus (pv), sternite (st), tergite (t). Scales = 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202498/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1174,1191,1052,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Projection in dorsal view with the basal half large and covered by long white setae, apical half straight and with few scattered black setae (
<figureCitation box="[223,292,1124,1148]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[310,1266,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[310,1267,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 4, Male proximal abdominal tergites, lateral view, setae not represented; Fig. 5, Male, dorsal projection of the first abdominal tergite, dorsal view; Fig. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 7, Male terminalia, lateral view. Ectoproct (ect), paramere (pa), pulvinus (pv), sternite (st), tergite (t). Scales = 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202498/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[276,292,1124,1148]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
); the ventral surface is concave along the entire length; apex with a small concavity at apex in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[222,290,1160,1184]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[310,1266,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[310,1267,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 4, Male proximal abdominal tergites, lateral view, setae not represented; Fig. 5, Male, dorsal projection of the first abdominal tergite, dorsal view; Fig. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 7, Male terminalia, lateral view. Ectoproct (ect), paramere (pa), pulvinus (pv), sternite (st), tergite (t). Scales = 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202498/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[275,290,1160,1184]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
), and with the ventral region elongated in lateral view. Tergite IX divided into two lateral plates by a dorsal longitudinal membranous area (
<figureCitation box="[593,664,1196,1220]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[310,1266,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[310,1267,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 4, Male proximal abdominal tergites, lateral view, setae not represented; Fig. 5, Male, dorsal projection of the first abdominal tergite, dorsal view; Fig. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 7, Male terminalia, lateral view. Ectoproct (ect), paramere (pa), pulvinus (pv), sternite (st), tergite (t). Scales = 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202498/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[648,664,1196,1220]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Sternite IX, completely dark brown; covered by long black setae (
<figureCitation box="[159,228,1232,1256]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[310,1266,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[310,1267,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 4, Male proximal abdominal tergites, lateral view, setae not represented; Fig. 5, Male, dorsal projection of the first abdominal tergite, dorsal view; Fig. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 7, Male terminalia, lateral view. Ectoproct (ect), paramere (pa), pulvinus (pv), sternite (st), tergite (t). Scales = 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202498/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[240,255,1232,1256]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">8</figureCitation>
); medial posterior border extended and with a small concavity in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1148,1216,1232,1256]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1200,1216,1232,1256]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ectoproct reddish brown and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[389,488,1268,1292]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[310,1266,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[310,1267,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 4, Male proximal abdominal tergites, lateral view, setae not represented; Fig. 5, Male, dorsal projection of the first abdominal tergite, dorsal view; Fig. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 7, Male terminalia, lateral view. Ectoproct (ect), paramere (pa), pulvinus (pv), sternite (st), tergite (t). Scales = 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202498/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">Fig. 6, 7</figureCitation>
). Pulvinus connected by a membrane to the ventral region of ectoproct; extremelly elongated and with apex curved and covered by black bristles, the gonosetae (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1156,1304,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[310,1266,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[310,1267,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 4, Male proximal abdominal tergites, lateral view, setae not represented; Fig. 5, Male, dorsal projection of the first abdominal tergite, dorsal view; Fig. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 7, Male terminalia, lateral view. Ectoproct (ect), paramere (pa), pulvinus (pv), sternite (st), tergite (t). Scales = 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202498/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">Fig. 6, 7</figureCitation>
). Gonarcus reduced and membranous (
<figureCitation box="[313,383,1340,1364]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[367,383,1340,1364]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Paramere very elongated, black, with apex curved (
<figureCitation box="[996,1095,1340,1364]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[310,1266,193,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[310,1267,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 4, Male proximal abdominal tergites, lateral view, setae not represented; Fig. 5, Male, dorsal projection of the first abdominal tergite, dorsal view; Fig. 6, Male terminalia, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 7, Male terminalia, lateral view. Ectoproct (ect), paramere (pa), pulvinus (pv), sternite (st), tergite (t). Scales = 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202498/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">Fig. 6, 7</figureCitation>
) and with surface completely covered by acuminate micro-projections (
<figureCitation box="[620,690,1376,1400]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[674,690,1376,1400]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pelta located between parameres and with long black setae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,1412,1436]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Membrane ventrally attached to the gonarcus folded forming the gonosaccus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" box="[151,1082,1448,1472]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
