<quantity box="[303,420,1448,1472]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.235" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="32.35">32.35 mm</quantity>
. Forewing length: 
<quantity box="[630,747,1448,1472]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.83" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="28.3">28.30 mm</quantity>
. Hindwing length: 
<quantity box="[961,1078,1448,1472]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.304" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="23.04">23.04 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1484,1508]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
<typeStatus box="[199,323,1484,1508]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">Paratypes</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
Male, similar to 
<typeStatus box="[520,618,1484,1508]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">holotype</typeStatus>
except for antenna with 
<number box="[895,923,1484,1508]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="51.0">51</number>
segments. Body length: 
<quantity box="[1201,1318,1484,1508]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.196" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="31.96">31.96 mm</quantity>
. Forewing length: 
<quantity box="[235,352,1520,1544]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.78" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="27.8">27.80 mm</quantity>
. Hindwing length: 
<quantity box="[567,684,1520,1544]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.29" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="22.9">22.90 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" box="[197,1343,1556,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Female: Head with the same color pattern; vertex with white pilosity; antenna with 
<number box="[1132,1224,1556,1580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="49.0" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="48.0">48 to 50</number>
segments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Thorax: one specimen with the same color pattern of the males except for a central yellow spot in the mesoscutellum and for the yellow mesosubscutellum, the other is slightly lighter; dorsal sclerites brown with a median longitudinal light-yellow stripe in the pro and mesonotum and light-yellow spots in the apical border of the meso and metaprescutum; pleural sclerites white with some light brown spots. Legs and wings (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1291,1700,1724]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,2010,2033]" captionTargetBox="[203,1362,232,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[185,1409,195,1987]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 1, Head, lateral view; Fig. 2, Antenna apex; Fig. 3, Fore and hindwing (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202497/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1277,1291,1700,1724]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) as in male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Abdomen similar to male just slightly lighter in one of the specimens. first abdominal tergite without the conical projection but with pale yellow lateral plates folded over the respective tergite (
<figureCitation box="[1073,1155,1772,1796]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1124,1155,1772,1796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Terminalia: tergite VIII prolonged downward laterally, with spiracles open over it (
<figureCitation box="[820,903,1808,1832]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[874,903,1808,1832]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); tergite IX divided into two lateral plates by a dorsal longitudinal membranous area, posterior border “S” shaped in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1157,1844,1868]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1128,1157,1844,1868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); ventrovalvae and distivalvae, covered with long setae, elongated, and touching each other in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1100,1183,1880,1904]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[1152,1183,1880,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
); ectoproct rounded in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[298,379,1916,1940]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1892,1915]" captionTargetBox="[225,1357,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1357,193,1854]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Fillus amazonicus n. sp., Fig. 8, Male sternite IX, ventral view; Fig. 9, Male genitalia, posteroventral view; Fig. 10, Female proximal abdominal tergites, dorsal view, setae not represented; Fig. 11, Female terminalia, lateral view; Fig. 12, Ventrovalvae and distivalvae, ventral view. Distivalvae (dv), ectoproct (ect), gonarcus (gc), lateral plate (lp), paramere (pa), pelta (plt), tergite (t), ventrovalvae (vv). Scales = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202499/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<number box="[350,379,1916,1940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="23" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
), linguella not visible.
</paragraph>
