<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="27">Bionomic data:</emphasis>
All specimens were collected using light traps placed in the canopy and near the ground in a forested area in Itapiranga municipality, Amazonas state, located in the central Amazon, on the north side of the Amazonas River. This is the first record of this genus to 
<collectingCountry box="[777,848,295,319]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, significantly expanding its distribution from 
<collectingCountry name="Argentina" pageId="5" pageNumber="27">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[247,351,333,357]" name="Paraguay" pageId="5" pageNumber="27">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
to Amazon Basin.
</paragraph>
